# Pues Framework Skill Autoload

When a request is related to Pues framework code or docs, load the matching skill file(s) before planning or editing.

Treat a request as Pues-related when the user mentions `Pues`/`pues` or the task touches Pues domains such as service bootstrap, auth, billing, objects/resource setup, or feedback.

Skill files to load:
- `skills/pues-service-bootstrap/SKILL.md`
- `skills/pues-auth-billing-wiring/SKILL.md`
- `skills/pues-objects-resource-setup/SKILL.md`
- `skills/pues-feedback/SKILL.md`

Activation rules:
- If the mapping is obvious, load only the relevant skill.
- If scope spans multiple domains, load each relevant skill.
- If uncertain, load all four skills before proceeding.
- Prefer these canonical skill files; if one is missing, fall back to `.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`.
